headline: The Bull Case For GoDaddy (GDDY) Could Change Following Raised Revenue Outlook and Aggressive Share Buyback
summary: GoDaddy Inc. recently reported its third quarter 2025 results, surpassing revenue and profit expectations, and raised its full-year 2025 revenue guidance to US$4.93 billion to US$4.95 billion, representing approximately 8% growth at the midpoint. An additional highlight is the company's completion of a US$767.27 million share buyback, reflecting a focus on capital returns alongside ongoing expansion of its cloud-based services for entrepreneurs.
